com.yworks.yfiles.view

Interface IVisualCreator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArcEdgeStyleRenderer, BevelNodeStyleRenderer, CollapsibleNodeStyleDecoratorRenderer, DefaultLabelStyleRenderer, DefaultPortCandidateDescriptor, GeneralPathNodeStyleRenderer, GridVisualCreator, IconLabelStyleRenderer, ImageNodeStyleRenderer, MemoryImageNodeStyleRenderer, OverviewGraphVisualCreator, PanelNodeStyleRenderer, PathBasedEdgeStyleRenderer, PolylineEdgeStyleRenderer, ShapeNodeStyleRenderer, ShinyPlateNodeStyleRenderer, TableNodeStyleRenderer, TemplateLabelStyleRenderer, TemplateNodeStyleRenderer, TemplatePortStyleRenderer, TemplateStripeStyleRenderer, VoidVisualCreator

    public interface IVisualCreator
    Factory interface which is used by implementations that know how to create Nodes for rendering into a given IRenderContext.
    See Also:
    CanvasControl, ICanvasObjectDescriptor, ICanvasObject

    • Method Detail

      • createVisual

        Node createVisual(IRenderContext context)
        This method is called by the framework to create a Node that will be included into the IRenderContext.

        CanvasControl uses this interface through the ICanvasObjectDescriptor to populate the visual canvas object tree.

        Parameters:
        context - The context that describes where the visual will be used.
        Returns:
        The visual to include in the canvas object visual tree. This may be null.
        See Also:
        updateVisual(IRenderContext, Node)

      • updateVisual

        Node updateVisual(IRenderContext context,
                  Node oldVisual)
        This method updates or replaces a previously created Node for inclusion in the IRenderContext.

        The CanvasControl uses this method to give implementations a chance to update an existing Visual that has previously been created by the same instance during a call to createVisual(IRenderContext). Implementation may update the oldVisual and return that same reference, or create a new visual and return the new instance or null.

        Parameters:
        context - The context that describes where the visual will be used in.
        oldVisual - The visual instance that had been returned the last time the createVisual(IRenderContext) method was called on this instance.
        Returns:
        oldVisual, if this instance modified the visual, or a new visual that should replace the existing one in the canvas object visual tree.
        See Also:
        createVisual(IRenderContext), ICanvasObjectDescriptor, CanvasControl
